1. Get docker vitess container, specify new version

2. Run container
docker run -it vitess/lite:v3.0

3. In other window check running container process
$ docker ps
CONTAINER ID        IMAGE               COMMAND             CREATED              STATUS              PORTS               NAMES
f0580d050ad3        vitess/lite:v3.0    "bash"              About a minute ago   Up About a minute                       happy_ellis

4. Copy vt config from container
$ docker cp f0580d050ad3:/vt .

5. Check vitess binaries in
$ ls -la vt/bin/
total 140M
-rwxr-xr-x. 1 ow ow 24M Dec  9 21:23 vtworker
-rwxr-xr-x. 1 ow ow 33M Dec  9 21:23 vttablet
-rwxr-xr-x. 1 ow ow 24M Dec  9 21:23 vtgate
-rwxr-xr-x. 1 ow ow 32M Dec  9 21:23 vtctld
-rwxr-xr-x. 1 ow ow 12M Dec  9 21:23 vtctlclient
-rwxr-xr-x. 1 ow ow 18M Dec  9 21:23 mysqlctld

6. Generate config
./gen vtworker
./gen vtgate
# etc.
